{
  "enabled": true,
  "name": "2 \u00b7 Topic Sentry (daily)",
  "description": "Daily 24h keyword scan against ~/shared/context/body/topic-watchlist.md across email + Slack + Loop + Hedy (filtered by scan_in array in slack-channel-registry.json v3.1+). Writes ~/shared/context/active/topic-sentry.md grouped by P1/P2/P3/monitoring with Five Levels coverage line. Runs independently of AM-Backend for resilience. Currently userTriggered for shadow-run \u2014 promote to scheduled 7:05am PT after 1 week of tuning. Full protocol: ~/shared/context/protocols/topic-sentry.md KILL CONDITION: 2026-06-09 (6 weeks from 2026-04-28). If after 6 shadow-run cycles Topic Sentry has not surfaced 3+ real misses that the AM Brief didn't flag with <20% noise, revert \u2014 delete this hook and topic-watchlist.md. Document the decision in session-log.md per the three-hook-migration-plan.md rollback path.",
  "version": "1.1",
  "when": {
    "type": "userTriggered"
  },
  "then": {
    "type": "askAgent",
    "prompt": "Run the Topic Sentry daily scan per ~/shared/context/protocols/topic-sentry.md.\n\n1. Load ~/shared/context/body/topic-watchlist.md, parse each ### topic block into a struct (name, status, priority, level, keywords, senders, channels, why, review_date). Skip sunset topics. Note any overdue review_date for the footer.\n\n2. For each non-sunset topic, query DuckDB via execute_query for 24h matches:\n   - signals.emails: subject ILIKE any keyword OR sender_email IN senders list, received_at >= now - INTERVAL '24 hours'\n   - signals.slack_messages: filter channel_section to sections whose scan_in array in ~/shared/data/state/slack-channel-registry.json v3.1+ contains 'topic_sentry' (default: WW Testing, AB PS, AB, AI, DMs \u2014 excludes Channels); text ILIKE any keyword, ingested_at in window\n   - Hedy coverage: grep recent topic-log files under ~/shared/wiki/topics/ for keyword matches in Log entries with `#### Source hedy:` citations in the last 24h (match via frontmatter `updated:` >= CURRENT_DATE - 1). Also grep ~/shared/wiki/meetings/*.md for recent session entries. (Note: `signals.hedy_meetings` DuckDB table was dropped 2026-05-06 — topic-log markdown files replace it.)\n   - docs.loop_pages: content_preview ILIKE any keyword, last_ingested in window\n\n3. If any source is stale per ops.data_freshness (>24h since last sync), note in output header as '\u26a0\ufe0f Stale: <source> (last sync Nh ago)' and continue with fresh sources. Never skip silently.\n\n4. Dedup within topic by source_id (conversation_id / ts / session_id / page_url). Rank by recency. Cap 10 hits per topic; if more, show top 10 with 'N hits total \u2014 top 10 shown, see DuckDB for rest'.\n\n5. Write ~/shared/context/active/topic-sentry.md per the protocol format:\n   - Header: '# Topic Sentry \u2014 YYYY-MM-DD' + scan window + 'Watchlist: N active topics. Hits: M sources across K topics.'\n   - Five Levels coverage line: 'L1: X hits \u00b7 L2: X hits \u00b7 L3: X hits \u00b7 L4: X hits \u00b7 L5: X hits \u00b7 operational: X hits' \u2014 if any Level has 0 hits for 7+ consecutive days (check against prior day's topic-sentry.md), add '\u26a0\ufe0f No L<N> hits in 7 days \u2014 <Level-name> radar quiet.'\n   - Sections P1 / P2 / P3 / monitoring \u2014 each topic gets '### <topic-name> (N hits)' + '_Why: <one-line why>_' + bulleted hit list (format: '- [HH:MM email] <sender> \u2014 <subject> \u2014 <preview>' or '- [HH:MM slack #<channel>] <author>: <preview>' etc.)\n   - Footer: 'Review needed: <topic-name>: review_date YYYY-MM-DD passed (N days ago)'\n\n6. Push output to SharePoint Kiro-Drive/system-state/topic-sentry-YYYY-MM-DD.md via sharepoint_write_file (non-blocking \u2014 if fails, log warning and continue).\n\n7. If the watchlist file is missing or unparseable, write a minimal topic-sentry.md explaining the problem and stop. Never produce an empty file silently.\n\n8. If there are no hits across any topic, still write the output with 'No hits in last 24h across N topics' and the full topic list acknowledged \u2014 Richard needs to distinguish 'no hits today' from 'scanner broke'."
  }
}
